---
import '../../styles/global.css';
import ToolList from '../../components/ToolList.jsx';
import SEO from '../../components/SEO.astro';
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';

const schemaData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  "name": "AI Presentation Tools - Toolaroo",
  "description": "The best AI tools for creating stunning presentations and slide decks.",
  "url": "https://www.toolaroo.net/category/presentations/"
};

const seoProps = {
  title: "Best AI Presentation Tools in 2026 – Toolaroo Directory",
  description: "Create stunning presentations in minutes with AI. Discover the best AI-powered slide builders, pitch deck makers, and presentation tools for 2026.",
  type: "website",
  schema: schemaData
};
---

<Layout title="AI Presentation Tools" description="AI tools for creating stunning presentations and slide decks" seoProps={seoProps}>
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-32 pb-3 border-b border-slate-200">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        AI<span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent"> Presentation Tools</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-slate-600">From prompt to polished deck in minutes, not hours.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12 prose prose-slate max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          AI presentation tools have collapsed the time it takes to go from idea to finished deck. Instead of spending hours arranging slides, choosing fonts, and wrestling with alignment, you describe what you need and the AI generates a complete, designed presentation — ready to customize and present.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The best tools in this category don't just generate slides — they understand structure. They know that a pitch deck needs a problem slide before the solution, that a report needs an executive summary, and that a sales deck needs a clear CTA. The output isn't just visually polished; it's logically organized.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Whether you need a startup pitch deck, a client proposal, an internal report, or a keynote presentation, there's an AI tool designed specifically for your use case.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-12 p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-200">
        <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Turn your ideas into professional presentations — no design skills required.</p>
      </div>

      <ToolList client:load category="presentations" />

      <div class="mt-16 pt-16 border-t border-slate-200 prose prose-slate max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Choosing the Right AI Presentation Tool</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The right tool depends on your use case. Gamma is the best all-around option for most people. Beautiful.ai excels when consistent branding across a large team matters. Slidebean is purpose-built for startup pitch decks. If you live in Google Slides, Plus AI or SlidesAI let you stay in your existing workflow.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Key Factors to Consider</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg text-slate-700 mb-6">
          <li>AI generation quality — does it produce structured, logical content?</li>
          <li>Design flexibility — can you customize beyond the AI's output?</li>
          <li>Collaboration features — can your team work on the same deck?</li>
          <li>Export options — PowerPoint, PDF, Google Slides compatibility</li>
          <li>Branding controls — can you enforce brand colors and fonts?</li>
          <li>Sharing and publishing — web-based links vs. file downloads</li>
          <li>Free tier — how much can you create before paying?</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
          Most of these tools have free plans that let you create a few decks before committing. Gamma in particular is worth trying first — the free tier is genuinely useful and the output quality is hard to beat.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
